##Overall Workflow
A modular node-based content pipeline which was built in Figma Weave, designed to produce 10 styled image prompts per garment.

---
##The stages
1. Product input - the garment images and a short brand/scene direction text are imported as the source inputs.
2. Brand visual guide - up to 6 reference photos feed into an LLM node alongside a custom visual guide generator prompt, which analyses the refernces and outputs a brand style guide specific to the brand.
3. Prompt generator - a second LLM node takes the brand style guide output plus the garment images and automatically writes 10 shoot-ready image prompts.

---
##The nodes
Nodes A - garment iamges
Node B - short brand/scene direction
Nodes C - up to 6 reference images
Node D - visual guide generator prompt
Node E - LLM node, which runs the visual and guide prompt with reference images and outputs detailed brand style guide
Node F1 & F2 - prompt assistants 
Node G1 & G2 - any LLM, which takes visual guide output + garment images and then outputs 5 detailed shoot prompts each
